From : {bold}Leto Kauler{nobold} <letok@netspace.net.au>
{p} {p}
Regarding AIO #28:  I really enjoyed reading the Bjorn Lynne
interview.  He is quite a legend and it was interesting to hear
how he started and what he's up to.
{p} {p}
It's also interested, and I think saddened, me with the news I've
been hearing about Gateway and Amiga, etc.  Not having all the
facts always leaves us shaky, but I generally agree with Chris'
"rants and raves about Gateway".  It is up to US to support what
is left of Amiga.  No producers are going to stay with Amiga long
if people aren't purchasing their products.
{p} {p}
From : {bold}Roger Buckley{nobold} <rogerbu@callnetuk.com>
{p} {p}
Whilst I unreservedly welcome the new AmigActive magazine I can't help but
wonder if this is a gamble doomed to failure. I don't know the gestation
period of a new magazine but it has evidently been dreamed up shortly after
the demise of CU Amiga and with the AmigaNG on the horizon ready to provide
for a new generation of Amiga fans purchasing the new machine. Sadly the
new machine does not appear to be a viable proposition and therefore the
main source of revenue for AA has been cut off before it really got going.
This is disappointing for all concerned as two lively and competing
magazines can only be of benefit to the whole Amiga community. The new
magazine appears to be well produced if a little thin but with plenty of
content. I particularly like the back2back articles. The only
disappointment for me was the CD with the 2 main software items, PPaint &
Octamed Sound Studio, having appeared on other cover CD's. PPaint 6.4 has
been superceded by PPaint 7 as far back as AFCD26, with the very same
version of Octamed on CUCD8 but there again if you haven't actually got
these programs they are both excellent value. I suppose it's down to
the lack of new software but the T-Zero Demo is fiddly to run as it needs
1.7MB+ to run which is not easy unless you have a graphics card.
All in all I rate it at 8/10 and hope to see an improvement in the future.
I've already placed my regular order at the newsagents and I'm pleased to
have 2 fixes a month instead of the one.
{p} {p}
