{bold}Andrew Crowe (Just-Amiga ML) Replies...{nobold}
{italic}Parnet? I don't think parnet is out for PC's. Anyway, there is software
around to link PC's and amiga's using a null modem cable (I think there's
some free on aminet too ;),
{p} {p}
Infact you could just use terminal programs to transfer data.{noitalic}
{p} {p}
{bold}Peter (Just-Amiga ML) Replies...{nobold}
{italic}The parnet cables only works Amiga<->Amiga .. you should use standard
laplink parrallel nullmodem cables, (or a standard serial nullmodem cable),
and a program like pc2amiga or twinexpress, or if you like you can use a
tcpip stack like Miami or AmiTCP/IP and a plip driver{noitalic}